pan><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 9:17:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23090.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tracking</span><hr size=1> Ok, granted...<br>
<br>
Indoors, you would probably be the master, almost as much so as those who have honed the skill all their lives in all enviornments (Read: Rangers, Druids, Bards, in that order).<br>
<br>
From a coding perspective though, it would make the most sense to give you near full tracking in your home zones and limited but existant in other dungeons and cities.  But then we'd have to be realistic, maybe you were only in Keladim for a few levels and havent returned since.  How can that be coded.. you dont really know those zones, do you?   Or maybe they're known like the back of your hand, or hilt of your dagger.  How can you even that out.  Maybe you know Neriak better than Keladim (And you're a dorf).<br>
<br>
Coding wise, it's not very easily done, I'd say.  Logical and probably worth a /feedback form, but I wouldnt see it being coded in for a while. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 9:24:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23090.topic&index=22>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~shadowcross/clip.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tracking</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> From a coding perspective though, it would make the most sense to give you near full tracking in your home zones and limited but existant in other dungeons and cities. But then we'd have to be realistic, maybe you were only in Keladim for a few levels and havent returned since. How can that be coded.. you dont really know those zones, do you? Or maybe they're known like the back of your hand, or hilt of your dagger. How can you even that out. Maybe you know Neriak better than Keladim (And you're a dorf).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
