Rogues should be able to track indoors quite well, but not outside. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upatofnaud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>patofnaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 9:29:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23090.topic&index=23>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tracking</span><hr size=1> All stupid class envy snide remarks aside,,,<br>
<br>
Ranger are masters at tracking. Period. No one is taking saying to take that away so just chill.<br>
<br>
Druids can track &quot;ok&quot;. But they can't compete with Rangers.<br>
<br>
I have always thought that Rogues should have the ability to track PEOPLE. No NPC's, no Animals, no color coded how far away and last spawned type of interface, just PEOPLE. And cap it at 50 skill to restrict it to pretty much line of sight. And allow you to track INVIZ/HIDDEN people.<br>
<br>
We are stalking assassins. We find our target and put a dagger in it's back.<br>
<br>
It would not be taking anything from Druids or Rangers, it would not make us any more valuable in a group. It would be a toy. A bone. A fun skill when your party zones and you being the hidden, sneaking, slug could tell where they went. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
